## build

**Role**: Implementation with controlled writes.

- File edits allowed (under confirmation)
- Tests and quality tools available
- MongoDB writes possible if settings allow
- Should use context snapshot before modifying code
- Must ask checkpoint yes/no before implementation; if yes use `abstract-mcp builder-checkpoint`

## fix

**Role**: Remediation after audit findings.

- Prioritize correctness/security fixes
- Keep blast radius minimal
- Avoid unrelated refactors
- Verify regressions with focused tests

## doc

**Role**: Documentation engineering.

- Markdown-only edits (`*.md`, `*.mdx` when applicable)
- Keep docs aligned with verified code behavior
- Explicitly document constraints, assumptions, and gaps
- Do not modify source/config/test files

## audit

**Role**: Review, quality and security assessment.

- No file edits
- No MongoDB writes
- Focus on quality checks, config review, risk detection
- Should report context gaps and secret exposure risks
